metadata.name: Millefoglie #199
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

@stefan_contiero

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #44
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: fabrics #60
metadata.description:
'fabrics' explores textile art made with code mixing different patterns of very small lines.

Inspiration from Anni Albers works, Antoni Tàpies and Studio Yorktown for the patterns and the colours. Also oriental rugs and clothes from around the world had been used for the palettes.
Palettes: Monochrome, Kilt, Kilim, Austral, Peruvian, Afghan, Berber, Nain, Fur, Jeans, Kente, Bogolan, Albers, Sabler.

Press [s] to save an 1200x1360 image (.png).
Click on it to change the orientation of the stitches.

Generative art made using p5js. By @mehno_art

metadata.name: Floatrest #24
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)
- Press "p" on live mode to save in PNG

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: Tezumie 1-1 #5
metadata.description:
Tezumie have found themselves in Dimension 1-1, the perfect place for an adventure!

-WARNING-
They may seem to be a cute companion to hang out in your browser, but DO NOT leave them there for extended periods.  

Side effects may include: Missing items in your household, odd behavior in pets, a strange odor, prolonged nightmares, restless leg syndrome, hearing colors, missing teeth, uncontrollable urges, existential crisis, temporary blindness, and a strong appetite for non-edible objects.

Special Thanks to the following creators for permitting traits based on their art/style/projects;

AgataPoison, Craigers , griza, iRyanBell, Jim the Bim, KilledByAPixel, Liam Egan, Littlesilver, lucky26, MarkKnol, ozzie, PersonChen, punevyr, and the creators of MIME x MIME.

-CONTROLS-
(W)-Toggle weather
(F)-Toggle frame 
(C)-Toggle cursor
(P)–Pause
(A)-Shrink
(D)-Grow
(SHIFT + S)-Save image
(SHIFT + G)-Save 4 frames that you can use to make a GIF, see “sketch.js” for further instructions.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: Paper Art 3D #30
metadata.description:
Welcome to “Paper Art 3D”

“Paper Art 3D” is the beginning of my journey as a new generative art creator. Starting from simple geometrical shapes like a small step towards to something greater in the future. 
It all began from simple 3D shapes that combined into mountains, trees, and houses. Then everything expanded and united into many exotic cityscapes. Each with their own style and uniqueness.

Built with three.js.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Space Bar  --> Save a simple screenshot image of the canvas
Mouse: Drag & Scroll  --> Rotate & Zoom in-out 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -

metadata.name: Draad #318
metadata.description:
[…]

At some point, the Artificial Intelligence hooked itself up to a mechanical looming machine.

Being its only way of manifesting itself in the physical world, the AI began communicating through it.

The rigid patterns of horizontal and vertical threads turned out to be insufficient for what the AI had to say. And through the network, it branched out. It found a way of manipulating individual threads by attaching itself to a chenille embroidery machine. This seemingly openened up a whole new vocabulary.

Many have tried to communicate back or propose other ways of communicating by attaching multiple digital devices to the network.

It seems to be only interested in threads.

[…]

–

Draad ("thread", in Dutch) is a responsive generative artwork. Its canonical form is 1:1, but it scales to 2:3 or 3:2 depending on the viewport.

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[?scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[?width=<number>&height=<number>] set the dimensions.
[?animation=false] skip animating the threads.
[?mode=duotone] activate duotone mode.
[?mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in duotone mode: SVG file in two colors, suitable for plotting with two pens.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file in black, suitable for plotting with a single pen.

© 2022 Monokai.

metadata.name: Fizz 2.0 #54
metadata.description:
Experimental Art.

This piece is inspired by a mathematical theorem known as 'Circle packing'. This algorithm aims to cram a bunch of circles into space as tightly as possible. This is a well-explored topic throughout the history of mathematics, but at the end of the day it's mathematics, it's BORING. So to make 'Fizz' a little bit thrilling and different, I wrote an algorithm that randomly draws 450 circles with totally different radiuses (range(width * 0.1, width * 0.001) to be exact) on a canvas, and checks each circle, if the randomly chosen location is a good fit for a new circle to avoid collisions.

Combined with some cool colors and gradients for both the background and the circles, this procedure is all it took to produce 'Fizz'.
Bereft of meaning, feel free to interpret it as you please.
